==Cost of ownership== Life cycle cost analysis by ZEV customers indicate that it costs approximately 60% less to drive a ZEV than to drive a gasoline fueled scooter of equal performance and cost to the ZEV electric if the bike is driven to the point of battery replacement. These customers report full costs not including depreciation of 12 cents/mile.{{Better source|date=January 2014}}<ref name=mmdpressrelease>{{citation|title=ZEV Delivers the ZEV10 LRC (225 km/140 m range) Fast Electric Motor Scooter|work=Press release|date=April 8, 2013|publisher=Z Electric Vehicle Corp.|url=http://www.mmdnewswire.com/zev-fast-electric-motor-scooter-129736.html}}</ref> Fuel costs on test bikes show fuel costs run about $.0127/mile or about $127 per 10,000 miles in the Ohio/WV/Pa area of the USA. With the large [[Battery (electricity)|battery]] capacity, the need to even charge more than one time a day is generally eliminated.<ref name="environmentfriendlystore">{{cite web|url=http://www.environmentfriendlystore.com/shop/zev_10_long_range_commuter_205_prd1.htm|title=Electric motorcycles, electric motorbikes, electric bikes and electric scooters|publisher=environmentfriendlystore.com|accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref>{{Better source|date=January 2014}}<ref name=mmdpressrelease/>
